narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes I would most definitely recommend this course
Hard, a lot of work, small class. You should e a fast reader. If you didn't likecanterbury tales you won't like this class.

Surprisingly good course. I took it for the pre-1800 requirement, but it became my favorite course all semester. I really liked having a small seminar format, and class discussion was much more interesting than I imagined it to be. This class confirmed my love for theater, and it was rewarding to examine Christianity from an academic perspective rather than from the church pews.If you aren't too keen on Middle English, there are also a lot of great modern works examined in the course, including various plays, movies, and videos of contemporary stage productions. Of course, we read our fair share of Middle English medieval plays, but it was much less Middle English than I expected.Overall a great course, and an enjoyable pre-1800 seminar.
